profile_positions.description:
Support the Design for Excellence (DfX) program globally for Philips Procurement, where each project investigates critically selected products through the entire “product lifecycle” process to build a “should cost” model. A DfX Project is usually a 10-12 weeks with multi-disciplinary team, to study the current products, do tear-downs, benchmark competition, invite suppliers for insights and go for supplier visits. In this role, it is critical to be independent and focus on larger goals with “TCO”. The process starts with receiving physical products and product data, several weeks prior to the start of the DfX start, to create preliminary cost models, which would be used to support the ideation process and will be further optimized as “target cost” till the end of the DfX project, and also creating a list of action points for the project team to execute within their own business environment.

Besides supporting DfX projects, other secondary responsibilities include :
•	Support various Commodity Teams with cost models for global Supplier Negotiation events ;
•	Support various R&D and Procurement Teams with “should cost” of critical components, with aPriori Application, if there are CAD models available, else with Cleansheet Application ;
•	Support the Licensing, Roll-out and acted as Helpdesk for Cleansheet Application for Philips ;
•	Support Workshops and Trainings on Cost Modeling, using Cleansheet and aPriori ;
•	Manage the DfX facilities for Global Cost Master team, DfX workshops and Tear-Downs ;

- Product Design of Glass products , typically for television screen (panel), cone (funnel) , neck ; for manufacturability - yield - cost for glass factories and also televisiopn tube factories ;

- Mechanical Design Team leader of Global projects ;

- Project leader of Global projects ;

- Account Manager for 2 Glass factories in Brazil , and 1 CRT factory in Mexico ;

Received "Innovation Award 2005".
